cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Sophia — the Wisdom Gate: a provenance-aware, verifier-gated reasoning layer that abstains instead of fabricating"
message: "If you use this software, dataset, or method, please cite it using this metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - alias: tomyimkc
    given-names: "Kin Cheong"
    family-names: "Yim"
    country: HK
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"  # TODO(author): register a free ORCID at orcid.org and add it here
repository-code: "https://github.com/tomyimkc/sophia-agi"
url: "https://tomyimkc.github.io/sophia-agi/"
abstract: >-
  Sophia is a provenance-aware, verifier-gated reasoning layer for large language
  models that abstains instead of fabricating. Given a claim, it verifies the claim
  against machine-readable sources and then accepts, abstains, or blocks. The system
  targets attribution hallucination — for example, an LLM falsely crediting an author,
  merging distinct intellectual traditions, or treating legendary figures as literal
  authors — and is evaluated under a pre-registered "no-overclaim" measurement gate
  (≥2 independent judge families, reported inter-judge agreement, ≥3 runs, and
  confidence intervals). Components include a belief/provenance graph with retraction
  and counterfactual analysis, deterministic and model-based verifiers, calibrated
  abstention, and a fail-closed governance contract.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - hallucination
  - attribution
  - abstention
  - selective prediction
  - provenance
  - retrieval-augmented generation
  - verifier-gated reasoning
  - trustworthy AI
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.9.0
date-released: 2026-06-22
